which has outperformed the market over the past  years the intellectual framework of this investment philosophy was introduced in the ’s through the teachings of ben graham and david dodd at columbia business school the basic premise of value investing is that most companies have a true intrinsic value to owners that can be determined and often becomes disconnected from current market prices profitable investments are made below intrinsic value this spread is what graham termed the “margin of safety” for the investor the value investing discipline has been practiced successfully by many of graham’s students including warren buffett walter schloss and irving kahn as well as by other disciples such as mario gabelli of gabelli asset management martin whitman of the third avenue value fund and joel greenblatt of gotham capital the talanta investment group llc seeks to define intrinsic value based on identified assets and proven cash flows it is this metric that ultimately determines the value of a company cash earned by a company provides the returns for the longterm investor irrespective of variations in shortterm market valuations john burr williams summed up this approach in his ’s classic the theory of investment value “if a man buys a security below its investment value he need never lose even if its price should fall at once because he can still hold for income and get a return above normal on his cost price but if he buys it above its investment value his only hope of avoiding a loss is to sell to someone else who must in turn take the loss in the form of insufficient income” – john burr williams october     talanta investment group inc all rights reserved talanta investment group inc client login why choose talanta investment group over the years talanta investment group llc has generated superior returns for clients by investing in overlooked opportunities in established niche businesses creating values for our clients in addition to focusing on investment oppo